Deck 30: Sultai Midrange Yorion
This is just a list of the strongest non-delve cards in Pioneer, with some cards to glue them together. That makes me interested in this right away. Yorion might be too cute, but it is rather powerful with Oath of Nissa. https://t.co/L3fYgFrn4L

Deck 29: Simic Reclamation
For those Wilderness Reclamation lovers (there are dozens of us)! Torrential Gearhulk casting Sublime Epiphany is a really fast way to close out a game, and the power level of cards in this deck is through the roof. This might be a real deck. https://t.co/XJlaXa4RAt

Deck 28: Seasons Past
Grim Tutor might be what this archetype needed to work in pioneer, but I am not sure it's enough. I'm not sure the tiny white splash is necessary, but the mythos and Kunoros solve problems the rest of the deck struggles with. Expect long games with this one. https://t.co/m47nWsaifm

My favourite list from this exercise. Possibility Storm + Lavinia/Teferi prevents your opponent from casting spells, and Lukka can turn any of your 2-drops into Agent of Treachery. Add Mox Amber, Fires of Invention and Yorion, and we have a deck. https://t.co/g0CdH7a6XM

full_text: Some of these decklists are not brand new ideas with fifty new cards, but they are a reminder of what one can do in this glorious format, especially since very few people (in a relative sense) have touched it since around February.

full_text: With the reminder that there are many more important things going on in the world (for the record - black lives matter, abolish the police, trans rights are human rights), my diversion from the world's chaos in the last 24 hours has been building thirty decks in pioneer! Thread:
